The paper proposes a method for constructing efficient deep graph neural networks (GNNs) using a recurrent neural network (RNN) to represent each input graph as a fixed point of a dynamical system. This approach is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). However, given the focus on deep learning and neural networks, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
